com.noctarius.tengi.core.serialization

Interface Enumerable<T extends Enum<T> & Enumerable<T>>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of the Enumerable which needs to be an Enum and an Enumerable

    public interface Enumerable<T extends Enum<T> & Enumerable<T>>

    The Enumerable interface is used to mark highly optimized but evolutionary Enum types. For support of evolution of enums the bundled serialization framework serializes an Enum using the name of the constant since ordinals tend to change based on reordering or adding new constants.

    Enumerables therefore have an additional value called flag which acts as a serialization constant type id, even if order or name of the constant changes or new constants are added the flag value can be preserved.

    Whenever a Enumerable is serialized the flag value will be written to the stream to optimize traffic and serialization speed.

      • value

        static <E extends Enumerable> E value(Class<E> type,
                                      int flag)
        This method supports to search for a Enumerable constant based on the given flag value. If no such constant can be found it will return null.
        Type Parameters:
        E - the type generic type of the Enumerable type
        Parameters:
        type - the Enumerable type to search in
        flag - the flag value (constant id)
        Returns:
        the constant according to the given flag if found, otherwise null
